My name is Dennis Caco and I am passionate about cars, racing, and making comic books and in 1998 I helped design Import Tuner Magazine, and combined my love for cars and comics to create Max Boost which was a monthly feature in the magazine. So, after we launched Import Tuner, we realized that Max Boost was a ABSOLUTE HIT with the readers, and MANY people subscribed to the magazine because of Max Boost.  And over the years, the magazine grew, and the Max Boost Fanbase grew with it.Now, 22 years later, this car culture has established itself and is as vibrant as ever.  Which is why I decided it was time to bring back Max Boost for the original generation of readers, as well as new fans alike.In 2019, we lauched a Volume 1 on another platform to bring Max Boost back!  We put the first 4 years (of 8 years) of Max Boost into a collectible volume and it was a success with over $54,000+ in pre-orders made and over 1000 books sold!So now we're back with Volume 2, continuing the story as it was first printed in Import Tuner Magazine!So I would hope that you would take a look, and "back this project", and help us make this Max Boost, Volume 2 a reality!  THANK GOD FOR THE FANS AND FRIENDS! -Despite that all those years I was in hibernation, I received a lot of love.  One of my greatest joys is meeting Max Boost Fans in real life, and / or getting Fan messages.In particular, I love getting  messages from those who were too young to drive when they first read Max Boost and now have tuner cars of their own. These stories kept reminding me that I should never have stopped drawing Max Boost- and if Max Boost, Volume 1 is successful -  I can bring Max Boost back for the next generation of tuner fans!Even though I took a mental break for over 10 years, inspiration came in an unlikely event.  My younger brother (he's 18 years younger than me) got into the tuner scene (on his own, I had no influence I swear!) and eventually asked me to bring him to the racetrack for the first time.And little did he know, combined with support from one of our original Max Boost + Autocannon crew Memo Quibrera, and jumping into Sam Rothschilds Honda Challenge Series championship winning CRX race car for the first time in YEARS - they reignited my need for speed, and my itch to bring Max Boost back!  So why am I on Indiegogo?I put over a decade of my life and sweat into Max Boost.  I invested everything I could to continue to make Max Boost for the people, and pursued the dream furiously.8 years into it, in 2006, Everything was going perfect and Max Boost was on a roll.  We got some serious momentum when we partnered with Playmates Toys (the Ninja Turtle Company) to make Max Boost Toys and we were even on our way to landing video games, and a deal for Saturday Morning Cartoons with Warner Bros.And then suddenly, the WB contract was cancelled -I hit rock bottom [Lost almost everything, and stopped drawing Max Boost to take a mental break.  I was devastated, as everything seemed to have fallen apart, and the hard work from so many was not actualized.And, well, my “short" mental break ended up being more than 10 years.I never stopped believing in Max Boost.  I never stopped loving cars, comics, and this culture.So I'm here, to put the control back in my hands - and build a MAX BOOST TEAM with YOU (yes YOU) - to launch more products that YOU WANT TO SEE without needing the studios or big names.  I realized with the power of community, we can actually do this independently.  So Max Boost Volume 2 is the SECOND step of MANY.  So, if this campaign is successful, it will allow us to continue with our NEXT STEPS:
Max Boost Volume 3
Animation
Toys
Netflix Show? :)
AND MORE....
Like my own life, Max Boost is a true Underdog story, where you're put up against all odds and still have to find a way to succeed.  Max Boost was simply a dream, and though hard work, long nights sleeping under drawing tables, and being a starving artist (literally), I was able to create something that fans worldwide loved. Max Boost is perfect for all gear heads, tuners, and comicbook fans looking for something that has deep roots and history in the Car Culture Or anyone who just love anime, cars, high speed hijinx, and a good ol' underdog story about a little hatch back “that could".So this is where YOU come in...Max Boost is ONLY available here, at a discount, with Bonuses in hopes you will become part of the Max Boost Fam reserve your very own limited first edition copies, today,Simply click below to "Back this Project" to keep this dream alive!Please contribute today, share with your friends, and become part of Team Max Boost!Drive Fast. Race Hard.Dennis Caco & Memo Quibrera, Marat Zabelinskiy, Dan Wilson, and the Max Boost Crew I could NOT have done this without so many people through the last 20 years and need to say THANK YOU!  (I am SURE I am forgetting a bunch of people, so please bear with me as I edit this from time to time)Of course, I need to start with my original "Racerette" and my wife Rachelle, and my son, Drake "Max" Caco, (yes his name is Max!),  and my very patient Mom, Dad my brothers Allan and Eric, and my super-sister Joann and her family.And of course, this would have never have happened without Albert Estacio and Collier Mclennan (Online Performance) convincing me to be the first DRAG GEN II Turbo Kit car for Herman Chan, and subsequently meeting Michael Ferrara from Turbo Magazine (now publisher of DSPORT), to shoot my Black Turbo Intergra GS-R  for a magazine feature back in 1995.From there I met published Kipp Kington (RIP) and the team at IGC - Ed Eng, Evan Griffey, and that crew that invited me to help them design a brand new magazine from scratch, which eventually became Import Tuner.  (I designed the original logo, cover concepts, and helped create the theme for Import Tuner).  Those were good 'ol days!So that's the beginning ...And since then I have met (and need to thank) so many friends and family:My number ones - my wife Rachelle and son, Drake "Max" CacoMemo Quibrera, Allan Deguzman, and Sam Rothschild for inspiring me to get back to the racetrack and bring Max Boost back to life.Sponsors: My studio and comic peeps:Nghia, Derek, Clydene Nee, Batton Lash, Joe Philips, Lex Wolfcraft, Chris NeuhahnCo-Workers and Friends; Memo Quibrera, Marat Zabelinskiy, Nick Coleman, April Estrada  Rich Langi, Carter Jung, Rick, Andres the Car Kid, Wes Walz, Artists and assistant artists:Rich, Jasen, Nghia, Eddie, Ray, Melissa, Derek, Conrad, Trace My OG race team:Sam Rothschild, Dan Wilson, Lee Lim, Ian Penaflorida and Family, Gabe, Tim T.Ground Zero Racing and Online Performance, Eddie from Dynamic Autosport and Ha (RIP) from Pann Autosport for being my very first retail customers in the mid 90's Influencers & social partners:
